title.narrative: INFANT YOUNG CHILD AND ADOLESCENT NUTRITION

description.narrative: Increased quality of relevant key nutrition services for infants, children and adolescents especially in the most vulnerable governorates and in humanitarian situations., which contributes to Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, all newborns, children, adolescents and women in Iraq access and equitably use affordable, high-impact health and nutrition services, especially the most vulnerable in humanitarian situations.
